{
  "stem": "27390.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, he wanted to leave to Palestine but it was very hard to-- to get an exit visa from Poland before the war.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You needed a passport.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "To get a passport, you had to pay a lot of money, also through a macher, these middlemen that arranged it with the government, with a government official.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then, to get into Palestine in those days was, as you know, there was a quota, I think, 1,500 or 15,000 per year people to enter Palestine, that's after the British government introduced the quota.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Palestine was out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So then my father wanted to go to South America, to the Argentine, he was considering to emigrate.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So but the rabbi advised him against it because most of the people that went to these counties became non-religious.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So that was all-- that was the reason why I didn't go to-- to-- why I didn't leave Poland before the war.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And also it was not so-- when a person lives in a country, born in a country, born in a town, and you-- you make a living, it's very hard to uproot yourself and to-- to go into the unknown and start all over again.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So most of the people carried on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A lot of people did emigrate but the majority didn't We didn't know what was waiting for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So that's how it was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Did you feel at home in Poland?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was my home, of course.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't know anything else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I didn't know anything else.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was my home and that I was amongst people, amongst Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everything was Jewish and everything what you wanted, schools and libraries and everything.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
